TASK COMPLETED - Traktion Personal Finance Management App

Completed: 2026-02-06
Agent: UI Generator

## Summary
Built complete Next.js application for Traktion - a personal finance management app with 4 main screens and full agent integration.

## Delivered Components

### 1. Main Dashboard (app/page.tsx) ✓
- Financial Health Score Card (circular progress with 78 score)
- Upcoming Payments Card (5 autopays with approve/delay actions)
- Subscription Summary Card ($111 monthly burn, 3 active subscriptions)
- Investment Snapshot Card ($45,280 portfolio value)
- Pending Settlements Card ($145.50 owed / $220 owed to you)
- Quick Actions Bar (Add Expense, Link Account, Set Reminder)

### 2. Autopays & Subscriptions Screen ✓
- Tabbed interface (Autopays | Subscriptions)
- Filter buttons (All, Pending, Approved)
- Payment cards with status badges and action buttons
- Subscription cards with pause/cancel toggles
- Calendar and filter toolbar

### 3. Shared Expenses Screen ✓
- Balance summary (You Owe, Owed to You, Net Balance)
- Group selector with dynamic filters
- Expense feed with settlement buttons
- Add Expense dialog
- Color-coded balance indicators

### 4. Investments Overview Screen ✓
- Portfolio summary card (Total Value, Daily Change, Change %)
- Holdings grid (5 stocks: AAPL, TSLA, MSFT, GOOGL, NVDA)
- Individual asset cards with performance metrics
- Allocation and Performance toolbar buttons

## Navigation System ✓
- Desktop: Fixed left sidebar (64px width)
- Mobile: Bottom navigation bar
- 4 nav items: Dashboard, Payments, Expenses, Investments
- Active tab highlighting with mint accent (#4ade80)

## Design System ✓
- Navy background (#1a2744)
- Mint accent (#4ade80) for CTAs and positive values
- Red (#ef4444) for amounts owed
- Gradient backgrounds on key cards
- Skeleton loading states
- Error alerts with retry buttons
- Empty states with friendly icons

## Agent Integration ✓
- All 8 agent IDs from workflow.json mapped
- callAIAgent() integration for all actions
- TypeScript interfaces based on agent purposes:
  * FinancialHealth
  * AutopayItem
  * Subscription
  * Investment
  * SharedExpense
  * DashboardData
- Action handlers for approve/delay/settle/cancel

## Technical Implementation ✓
- Single file solution (all components inline in app/page.tsx)
- React hooks (useState, useEffect)
- react-icons/fi for all icons (NO lucide-react)
- shadcn/ui components (Card, Button, Badge, Dialog, Tabs, etc.)
- Responsive grid layouts
- Clean JSON parsing ready for agent responses
- Error handling with retry functionality
- Loading states with skeletons

## Mock Data Included ✓
- Financial health score: 78 (trending up)
- 5 autopay items (2 pending, 2 approved)
- 4 subscriptions (3 active, 1 paused)
- 5 investment holdings
- 4 shared expenses (3 unsettled)
- Realistic dollar amounts and dates

